NORMALISED EXTRACT
Canonical strict regex (ECMAScript / JavaScript):
^M{0,3}(CM|CD|D?C{0,3})(XC|XL|L?X{0,3})(IX|IV|V?I{0,3})$

Explanation of groups:
- M{0,3}: thousands — allow 0 to 3 M's (0..3000)
- (CM|CD|D?C{0,3}): hundreds — 900 (CM), 400 (CD), or optional D (500) followed by 0..3 C's (0..800)
- (XC|XL|L?X{0,3}): tens — 90 (XC), 40 (XL), or optional L (50) plus 0..3 X's
- (IX|IV|V?I{0,3}): ones — 9 (IX), 4 (IV), or optional V (5) plus 0..3 I's

Use cases:
- Use this regex to reject malformed Roman numerals prior to parsing and to ensure round-trip correctness when fromRoman must accept only canonical forms.

